metadata.name: Step by Step #25
metadata.description:
Step by Step explores the feeling of being stuck, confined - walking the path ahead of you often only seeing the immediate next step until exhaustion. We all feel this way from time to time — in our lives, jobs, bodies, situations — yet in our search for something, we shouldn't forget that there can still be beauty along the path.

The project takes some inspiration from Henri Matisse, both in the aesthetics of his later works (i.e. the "Cut Outs") and metaphorically in the sense that he had underwent medical treatment which left him wheelchair- or bed-bound towards the later part of his life, forcing him to give up painting, yet in his exploration of this new creative medium which involved cutting paper and pinning them up, his unorthodox work went on to become the most transformative of his career.

Released as part of the 4th edition of the Cure³ Parkinson's cure fundraiser exhibition organized by Artwise Curators and Bonhams as part of a specially comissioned selection of generative artists minting NFTs, curated by Foteini Valeonti and Alex Estorick with the support of fx(hash) at Bonhams, London from 13-17th January 2023.

---
33% of primary sales and 3% of secondary sales will be donated on-chain to Cure Parkinson’s
---

Controls:
• 'R' regenerates the piece (e.g. in case the window size changes)

Made in p5js
Created Jan 2023
Artist: Yazid

metadata.name: Zusammen #55
metadata.description:
The flow of colors across an infinitely maleable grid. Zusammen is built using a framebuffer setup in p5js sampling a rendered direction field to determine the pixel "push" direction, speed, and offsets.

You can run this in fullscreen as instructed below. Doing so will render at the browser's width and height, which will look quite different from the preview version, but will still use the same colors and rules as your token. This can be useful for making wallpapers etc.

You can also continue to run the simulation after it has stopped by hitting the spacebar. This will allow you to further explore the infinite generative space of the piece.

Made with p5js.

Double click to download
Add &highres=true to the URL to get a higher resolution output
Add &fullscreen=true to render to the browser size. N.B. outputs will be somewhat different than the regular view

license information in license.md

metadata.name: Stitched #45
metadata.description:
You are the product of countless tiny decisions taken over the course of your life. Stitched is an attempt to visualize one’s current self as a product of the myriad forking paths available to us. It is best appreciated in animated format: the latent structure unfolds in time; the past gradually fades away, tinted and obscure. 

Past decisions and missed opportunities leave a trail on the present. Psychology affects what you explore: drive controls how frequent one changes direction; indecisive mints explore many loose ends; balanced mints match complementary colours.

Stitched is adaptive to arbitrary screen resolution and aspect ratio, and best appreciated at high resolution. It initially renders with a large step size in time; pause and unpause to watch it unfold more gradually.

controls:

mouse click or space bar: pause / unpause / reset animation
s: save current frame

Inspired by The Garden of Forking Paths by Borges and stylistically by French and Russian Impressionists, and Autoglyphs by Larva Labs.

metadata.name: Faltantrieb #26
metadata.description:
A simple particle system, folded, convolved, distorted and decorated into something wild and beautiful.

Made with p5js.

Double click to download
Add ?highres=true to the URL to get a higher resolution output (be aware that this will require a powerful computer)

Please note that this token has been optimized for Chrome. It will work in firefox but is much slower at generating an output and uses fewer particles.
